                            <comment id="486997" author="adilger" created="Sun, 8 Feb 2026 20:32:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19832&quot; title=&quot;e2fsprogs m_assume_prezeroed test fails on Ubuntu 24.04&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19832&quot;&gt;LU-19832&lt;/a&gt; is about breakage on Ubuntu with dash, though in e2fsprogs. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="486996" author="JIRAUSER18433" created="Sun, 8 Feb 2026 17:08:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;sh should be replaced with bash generally. Lustre scripts typically have too many bash-isms to work well on Debian or Ubuntu, which link sh to dash.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
